  MF2:  Resolved resonance range  (RRR)                           6329 1451   72
       The RRR was generated with TARES-1.31, compiled on         6329 1451   73
       12-10-2015 11:58:11 PM at Villingen  , Switzerland. The RRR6329 1451   74
       expands from 0 to 3.648203E+2 eV. A total of               6329 1451   75
       2 l-values are used and 200 resonances. The resonance      6329 1451   76
       formalism is multi-level Breit Wigner (MLBW).              6329 1451   77
       The ladder approach from the CALENDF code is used to       6329 1451   78
       generate statistical resonances in the unresolved          6329 1451   79
       resonance range. Therefore, the URR is translated into     6329 1451   80
       resolved resonance range. Explanations about the method    6329 1451   81
       can be found in the CALENDF manual: CEA-Report CEA-R-6277  6329 1451   82
       "CALENDF-2010: User manual" by J.C. Sublet, P. Ribon and   6329 1451   83
       M. Coste-Delcaux.                                          6329 1451   84
       The method of creating statistical resonances in the       6329 1451   85
       URR region is described in: "From average parameters to    6329 1451   86
       statistical resolved resonances", D. Rochman et al.,       6329 1451   87
       Annals of Nucl. Ene. 51 (2013) 60.                         6329 1451   88
       The s-wave average level spacing is 0.28005 eV and         6329 1451   89
       the s-wave neutron strength is 0.0007951 1e-4.             6329 1451   90
                                                                  6329 1451   91
  MF32: Covariance file for resonance parameters                  6329 1451   92
        The compact format is used to represent the covariance    6329 1451   93
        information on the resonance parameters. Uncertainties    6329 1451   94
        come from compilations, EXFOR or existing libraries and   6329 1451   95
        correlations between parameters are obtained following    6329 1451   96
        the method presented in NIM/A 589 (2008) 85.              6329 1451   97
