***************************** T A L Y S **************************6329 1451  153
                                                                  6329 1451  154
TALYS is a computer code system for the prediction and analysis   6329 1451  155
of nuclear reactions. TALYS simulates reactions that involve      6329 1451  156
neutrons, gamma-rays, protons, deuterons, tritons, helions and    6329 1451  157
alpha-particles, in the 1 keV - 200 MeV energy range. This is     6329 1451  158
achieved by implementing a suite of nuclear reaction models into  6329 1451  159
a single code system. This nuclear data file is based on a        6329 1451  160
theoretical analysis that utilizes the optical model, compound    6329 1451  161
nucleus statistical theory, fission, direct reactions and         6329 1451  162
pre-equilibrium processes, in combination with databases and      6329 1451  163
models for nuclear structure. The following output of TALYS is    6329 1451  164
stored in this data file:                                         6329 1451  165
                                                                  6329 1451  166
- Total, elastic and non-elastic cross sections                   6329 1451  167
- Inelastic cross sections to discrete states                     6329 1451  168
- Exclusive channel cross sections, e.g. (n,g), (n,2n), (n,np),.. 6329 1451  169
- Inelastic scattering angular distributions to discrete states   6329 1451  170
- Exclusive channel energy spectra                                6329 1451  171
- Exclusive channel double-differential spectra                   6329 1451  172
- Exclusive gamma production for discrete states and continuum    6329 1451  173
- Elastic scattering angular distributions                        6329 1451  174
- Recoil data                                                     6329 1451  175
- Total particle cross sections, e.g. (n,xn), (n,xp),..           6329 1451  176
- Total particle energy spectra                                   6329 1451  177
- Total particle double-differential spectra                      6329 1451  178
- Isomeric and ground state cross sections                        6329 1451  179
- Residual production cross sections                              6329 1451  180
                                                                  6329 1451  181
For a description of the used nuclear models and their            6329 1451  182
parameterization we refer to [kon12]. If for this specific        6329 1451  183
nuclide we deviate from the global parameterization, it is made   6329 1451  184
explicit above under Nuclide Specific Information.                6329 1451  185
                                                                  6329 1451  186
***************** F I L E   I N F O R M A T I O N ****************6329 1451  187
